<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245278>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 7. Habitus Altica species: 1, A. aenea (Olivier) (Australia); 2. A. aenea (Sumatra); 3. A. birmanensis (Jacoby); 4, A. caerulea (Olivier); 5, A. corrusca (Erichson); 6, A. cyanea Weber; 7, A. gravida (Blackburn)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245278/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245279>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 14. Head Altica species: 8, A. aenea (Olivier) (Australia); 9. A. aenea (Sumatra); 10. A. birmanensis (Jacoby); 11, A. caerulea (Olivier); 12, A. corrusca (Erichson); 13, A. cyanea Weber; 14, A. gravida (Blackburn)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245279/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245280>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19 – 22. Altica species: 19, A. gravida (Blackburn), prothoracic venter; 20, A. corrusca (Erichson), thoracic venter; 21, A. gravida, pterothoracic venter; 22, A. gravida, male abdominal venter." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245280/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245282>
    dc:description "FIGURES 27 – 29. Altica species, male genitalia (penis in ventral, dorsal and lateral view): 27, A. corrusca (Erichson); 28, A. cyanea Weber; 29, A. gravida (Blackburn)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245282/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245283>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30 – 31. Altica species, female genitalia (vaginal palpi, spermatheca and sternite VIII): 30, A. corrusca (Erichson); 31, A. gravida (Blackburn)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245283/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245284>
    dc:description "FIGURES 62 – 76. Altica species, spermathecae: 62, A. aenea (Olivier) (Northern Territory, Australia); 63, A. aenea (New South Wales, Australia); 64, A. aenea (north Queensland, Australia); 65, A. birmanensis (Jacoby) (West Java); 66, A. birmanensis (Sulawesi); 67, A. caerulea (Olivier) (Northern Territory); 68, A. caerulea (Torres Straits); 69, A. corrusca (Erichson) (New South Wales); 70, A. corrusca (Tasmania); 71, A. cyanea Weber (lectotype, Sumatra); 72, A. cyanea (West Java); 73, A. gravida (Blackburn) (Victoria, Australia); 74, A. gravida (eastern New South Wales); 75, A. gravida (eastern New South Wales); 76, A. gravida (western New South Wales). Drawn to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245284/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245288>
    dc:description "FIGURE 83. Altica gravida (Blackburn): larval defoliation of Myriophyllum papillosum, Barmah National Park, Victoria (photo: K Ward)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245288/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

